    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1049"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1049">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 261: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-22">July 22,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 728. Repeated information Saigon 102.
                        <persName corresp="#p_TVC1">Tran Van Van</persName>, former Minister of
                    National Economy and claiming to be Geneva observer of Vietnamese Front of
                    National Safety (Hoa Hao, Cao Dai, Binh Xuyen, and Catholics) left copies of
                    prise de position with <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> this
                        morning.<note n="1" xml:id="d1049fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TVC1">Van</persName> supports position Vietnamese
                    delegation at conference, but criticizes it for not walking out at last minute.
                    He attacks French Colonialists and Viet Minh for collusion and sell-out to
                    Vietnam, accusing former of wishing to hold on to richest part of country,
                    states that the Front will take up the fight for independence and unity.</p>
                <p>Statement being pouched Department and Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
